?TOP STORIES
US REP BARTON UNVEILS EMERGNCY ELECTRICITY LEGISLATION

U.S. Rep. Joe Barton, R-Texas, formally unveiled Friday an "Emergency 
Electricity Act" designed to provide relief for California and Western states 
this summer.

AS SHOCKERS GO, PG&E BANKRUPTCY IS BIG ONE

A day after California Gov. Gray Davis went on television to announce a rate 
hike aimed at easing the state's energy crisis by helping its ailing 
utilities, one of the companies filed for bankruptcy.

POWER GRID BATTLES REACH TURNING POINT IN U.S. SOUTH

A battle over who will control major power lines in the U.S. South is taking 
a new direction.

NEVADA GOVERNOR TO UNVEIL EXPANSIVE NEW PLANS FOR POWER PLANTS

Gov. Kenny Guinn today will detail plans for new power plant construction in 
Nevada, the result of a streamlined permitting process that is part of his 
Nevada Energy Protection Plan.

-FLORIDA LEGISLATURE SEEMS UNLIKELY TO PASS ELECTRICITY DEREGULATION

Prospects for passing a law this year to open Florida's wholesale electricity 
market to competition are dimming quickly. 


